    <bug_when>2014-12-01 18:39:18 -0500</bug_when>
    <thetext>The array type is captured inside a CaptureBinding18. I see nothing prohibiting a capture of an array type, moreover, the comment in JLS 4.9 explicitly mentions: &quot;However, capture conversion can lead to the creation of type variables whose bounds are more general, such as array types&quot;.

The point where things go wrong is when we reduce this constraint:
  Z#0-E#0 extends Object[] &lt;: Exception

CaptureBinding18.isCompatibleWith() delegates to super which then asks CaptureBinding18.isEquivalentWith() which blatantly wrongly answers true.

Both methods need to be improved (I&apos;m amazed how far we got with these implementations...).

I&apos;m trying to combine the best from
 - CaptureBinding (which only has one bound)
 - IntersectionTypeBinding18 (which doesn&apos;t handle array bounds)

Tests pending.</thetext>
